{
  "texts": [
    "On our mobile devices and computers, text data usually takes the form of digital newspaper articles, webpages, blogs, Short Message Service (SMS) text, e-books, etc.",
    "Almost all of these text data are non-technical and based on spoken languages or are derivatives of spoken languages.",
    "Since these languages are a part of everyday interaction, there is a lot of scope to use the data from it, which is exactly what NLP methods are built for.",
    "One of the main requirements for NLP models to succeed is the availability of large amounts of text data, also referred to as corpora, for model training purposes.",
    "Since non-technical data is available in abundance, it is not a problem for the NLP pipeline."
  ]
}